<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1436,151,284]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,151,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1906" box="[328,578,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscofasciata">
<emphasis box="[328,578,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Rhotana fuscofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Zelazny &amp; Webb, 2011" authorityName="Zelazny &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2011" box="[704,857,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirashimai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[704,857,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">R. hirashimai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[864,951,152,175]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from Borneo in structure and coloration. It can be recognized by the lack of a red mark around the last subcostal sector of the forewings, the shape and position of the hindwing marks, by the shorter lateral projections of the male pygofer and by the shape of the apical part of the male aedeagus.
</paragraph>
